ext", "text": ", (S, Msb, K,) of which last"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "maraAHimu", "text_ar": "مَرَاحِمُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "is pl., (TA,) [all inf. ns.; when used as simple substs. signifying"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Mercy, pity,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "compassion;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "i. e.]"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "tenderness"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(S, Msb, K, and Bd on the"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "basomalap", "text_ar": "بَسْمَلَة"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ")"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "of heart;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(Bd ibid.;) and"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "inclination to favour,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(S, Msb, K,) or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "inclination requiring the exercise of favour and beneficence:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(Bd ubi suprà:) and"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "pardon,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "forgiveness:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(K:) accord. to Er-Rághib,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "raHomapN", "text_ar": "رَحْمَةٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "signifies"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "tenderness requiring the exercise of beneficence towards the object thereof:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and it is used sometimes as meaning"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "tenderness divested of any other attribute:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and sometimes as meaning"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "beneficence divested of tenderness;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "as when it is used as an attribute of the Creator: when used as an attribute of men, it means"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "tenderness,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "inclination to favour"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "without necessarily implying beneficence"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]: accord. to El-Káshánee, it is of two kinds; namely, gratuitous, and obligatory: the former is that which pours forth favours, or benefits, antecedently to works; and this is the"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "rHmp", "text_ar": "رحمة"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "that embraces everything: the obligatory is that which is promised to the pious and the doers of good, in the Kur vii. 155 and vii. 54: but this, he says, is included in the gratuitous, because the promise to bestow it for works is purely gratuitous: accord. to the explanation of the Imám Aboo-Is-hák Ahmad Ibn-Mohammad-Ibn-Ibráheem Eth-Thaalebee, it is God's"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "desire to do good to the deserving thereof;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "so that it is an essential attribute: or the"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "abstaining from punishing him who deserves punishment, and doing good to him who does not deserve"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "this"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]; so that it is an attribute of operation. (TA.) The saying in the Kur [xxi. 75]"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "waA^adoxalonaAhu", "text_ar": "وَاَدْخَلْنَاهُ"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "fiY raHomatinaA", "text_ar": "فِى رَحْمَتِنَا"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(tropical:)  ["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "And we caused him to enter into our mercy"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "] is tropical: so says IJ. (TA.) ―         -b2-"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "waA@ll~`hu", "text_ar": "وَا@للّٰهُ"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "yaxotaS~u biraHomatihi mano ya$aA='u", "text_ar": "يَخْتَصُّ بِرَحْمَتِهِ مَنْ يَشَا=ءُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", in the Kur [ii. 99 and iii. 67], means (assumed tropical:)  ["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "And God distinguishes"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "with his gift of prophecy"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "whom He will"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "], or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "his prophetic office"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "commission."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(K, * TA.) ―         -b3-"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "raHomapN", "text_ar": "رَحْمَةٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "also means (assumed tropical:)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Sustenance,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or the"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "means of subsistence:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "this is said to be its meaning as used in the Kur xli. 50. (TA.) ―         -b4-  And (assumed tropical:)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Rain:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(TA:) so in the Kur vii. 55. (Bd, Jel.) ―         -b5-  And (assumed tropical:)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Plenty;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "abundance of herbage,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "of the goods, conveniences,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "comforts, of life:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "so in the Kur x. 22 and xxx. 35. (TA.)"}], "source_refs": ["S", "Msb", "K", "Sb", "TA"]}]}, "classical_definitions": null, "translations_attribution": {"model": "qwen36-35b-heretic", "generated_date": "2026-05-18", "pipeline_version": "words.translation.v1.spark"}}